### Instruction:
How do you align a row of divs to the right using flex in css?  Show me an example.

### Response:

To align a row of divs to the right using flex in CSS, you can use the following code:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
}

.item {
  flex-grow: 1;
}
```
This will create a container with all its child elements aligned to the right using the `display: flex` property. The child elements are given a `flex-grow` value of `1`, which means they will take up equal amounts of space within the container.

Here's an example HTML code that demonstrates this:
```html
<div class="container">
  <div class="item">Item 1</div>
  <div class="item">Item 2</div>
  <div class="item">Item 3</div>
</div>
```
And here's the corresponding CSS code:
```css
.container {
  display: flex;
}

.item {
  flex-grow: 1;
}
```
This will align the row of divs to the right using the `display: flex` property and the `flex-grow` value of `1` for each child element.
